WEBVTT

00:01.210 --> 00:03.190
LINDSAY: Previously on
"The Practice"...

00:03.190 --> 00:05.090
- You want to hire me
to defend you

00:05.090 --> 00:06.200
in a sexual harassment case?

00:06.200 --> 00:08.060
Don't you think
that's a little strange?

00:08.060 --> 00:10.050
- Why?
You're an excellent attorney.

00:10.050 --> 00:12.150
- Who you've had
erotic dreams about.

00:12.150 --> 00:14.040
- Oh, please.
If I had a dime

00:14.040 --> 00:16.160
for every erotic dream
I'd ever had, forget it.

00:16.160 --> 00:20.000
- Is it possible that you
weren't that great a clerk?

00:20.000 --> 00:21.170
- Well, I don't think
she had the opportunity

00:21.170 --> 00:23.210
to really know whether I was
a good clerk or not.

00:23.210 --> 00:25.140
- And why is that?

00:25.140 --> 00:28.040
- The only thing that transpired
and her chambers was sex.

00:28.040 --> 00:30.040
We probably made love

00:30.040 --> 00:32.140
two to three times a day,
sometimes four.

00:32.140 --> 00:35.190
- Listen, maybe you want to get
a glass of champagne later?

00:35.190 --> 00:37.010
Toast our victory.

00:37.010 --> 00:40.020
- Sure.
- Tell me, Jimmy,

00:40.020 --> 00:43.090
do you typically toast victory
with all of your clients?

00:43.090 --> 00:48.110
Or did all that sex
talk make you curious?

00:48.110 --> 00:51.150
- We don't want this one.
- Why?

00:51.150 --> 00:54.100
- The victim is a nun,
stabbed 30 times--

00:54.100 --> 00:57.000
- Oh, come on,
you love these cases.

00:57.000 --> 00:58.190
- Plus, the district
attorney is my roommate.

00:58.190 --> 01:00.210
That's grounds for
disqualification, right there.

01:00.210 --> 01:04.019
- Ms. Gamble, you are going
to put this man in jail,

01:04.019 --> 01:05.140
aren't you?

01:05.140 --> 01:08.050
- Yes, I'm definitely
gonna do that.

01:08.050 --> 01:10.040
- We got a shot
at getting this case kicked.

01:10.040 --> 01:12.160
- Excuse me?
- Fourth amendment.

01:12.160 --> 01:14.060
Could be a bogus search.

01:14.060 --> 01:16.230
- The search
of the closet was illegal.

01:16.230 --> 01:21.000
The contents are inadmissible.
He is free to go.

01:21.000 --> 01:23.220
[murmuring]

01:25.090 --> 01:28.090
<i>[soft music]</i>

01:28.090 --> 01:36.070
<i>♪</i> ♪

01:42.090 --> 01:45.210
- Bobby come in yet?
- No, not yet.

01:45.210 --> 01:47.080
What's wrong, Jimmy?

01:47.080 --> 01:49.020
- Nothing.

01:50.090 --> 01:52.090
[door opens]

01:52.090 --> 01:54.100
- Bobby, can I see you
a second?

01:54.100 --> 01:56.080
- Now?
- Now.

01:56.080 --> 01:58.060
- What's wrong?

02:01.010 --> 02:02.190
- I was on the Internet,
last night.

02:02.190 --> 02:04.220
You know,
just killing time.

02:04.220 --> 02:06.150
Privacy of my own home.

02:06.150 --> 02:08.130
I don't know
what I was thinking.

02:08.130 --> 02:09.169
- Jimmy.

02:09.169 --> 02:11.160
- I clicked onto a web page.

02:11.160 --> 02:13.040
It was about hidden cameras.

02:13.040 --> 02:14.170
I figured, what the heck.

02:14.170 --> 02:16.150
- What, you saw
some girly pictures?

02:16.150 --> 02:20.060
- Videos--
and not just any girly videos.

02:20.060 --> 02:23.080
Lucy was in one of them.

02:23.080 --> 02:25.170
- Lucy?

02:25.170 --> 02:27.080
[whispers]
Our Lucy?

02:27.080 --> 02:29.130
- Yeah.
- You're sure?

02:29.130 --> 02:32.210
- I downloaded it to show you.

02:35.090 --> 02:37.200
[computer whirrs]

02:40.210 --> 02:43.010
It's kind of like psycho.

02:43.010 --> 02:45.050
No,
nobody gets hurt or nothing.

02:48.230 --> 02:50.210
Think she knows about this?

02:50.210 --> 02:52.100
- That's not Lucy.

02:52.100 --> 02:54.230
I mean, that's Lucy

02:54.230 --> 02:57.210
but she--she wouldn't, um--

03:00.090 --> 03:01.120
Turn it off.

03:01.120 --> 03:04.000
- There's more.
- Jimmy.

03:06.160 --> 03:10.180
- What should I do?
- You got to tell her.

03:10.180 --> 03:12.190
- Maybe <i>you</i> should tell her.

03:12.190 --> 03:13.190
[door opens]

03:13.190 --> 03:15.120
What?
- What?

03:15.120 --> 03:16.220
- Just bringing in the mail.

03:16.220 --> 03:19.020
- Oh, you can just, uh,
put it on the desk.

03:19.020 --> 03:22.060
- Yeah, right on the desk.
The desk is good.

03:22.060 --> 03:25.010
- Okay?

03:25.010 --> 03:27.080
What's wrong?
both: Nothing.

03:27.080 --> 03:28.230
- The desk is fine.

03:28.230 --> 03:30.210
- I'll take the mail.

03:32.100 --> 03:34.040
- Okay.

03:40.090 --> 03:43.050
[door closes]

03:43.050 --> 03:47.020
- I don't think I could ever
look at her the same again.

03:47.020 --> 03:49.220
- I know I can't.

03:49.220 --> 03:51.040
[sighs]

03:51.040 --> 03:54.040
<i>[upbeat dramatic music]</i>

03:54.040 --> 04:02.020
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:40.140 --> 04:42.080
- I already testified once.

04:42.080 --> 04:45.070
- That was at the prelim.
I explained this, Gary.

04:45.070 --> 04:47.210
- You can't just
go with the other witnesses?

04:47.210 --> 04:50.050
- You're the only eyewitness.

04:50.050 --> 04:52.110
- [sighs]
Okay.

04:52.110 --> 04:56.010
- You want to go over it again?
- No, I-I got it.

04:56.010 --> 04:57.080
I'm okay.

04:57.080 --> 05:02.060
- Gary,
I know this is hard.

05:02.060 --> 05:03.230
- You know?

05:03.230 --> 05:08.080
You ever see your mother
get shot, Miss Gamble?

05:08.080 --> 05:11.110
- I'll try to keep it short.

05:11.110 --> 05:13.190
- Does my father
have to be there?

05:13.190 --> 05:17.190
- Gary,
he's the defendant.

05:17.190 --> 05:23.130
<i>♪</i> ♪

05:28.060 --> 05:30.070
- So,
you didn't know about this?

05:32.040 --> 05:34.210
I didn't think so.

05:34.210 --> 05:36.090
[door opens]

05:36.090 --> 05:38.130
- Hey, what's going on?

05:38.130 --> 05:41.090
- Lindsay,
could you excuse us for a sec?

05:41.090 --> 05:42.200
- Sure.

05:44.170 --> 05:48.120
- How could this happen?

05:48.120 --> 05:50.090
- You never made any videos?

05:50.090 --> 05:51.180
- No.

05:51.180 --> 05:55.020
- And you don't have
any roommates?

05:55.020 --> 05:56.130
Okay.

05:56.130 --> 05:59.070
Let's go check out
your apartment.

06:02.080 --> 06:04.140
- When I arrived at the scene,
I found the defendant,

06:04.140 --> 06:07.040
Gordon Armbrust,
seated on the living room sofa

06:07.040 --> 06:08.090
with his head in his hands.

06:08.090 --> 06:10.070
- What else did you see,
Detective?

06:10.070 --> 06:11.120
- The victim,
Charlotte Armbrust.

06:11.120 --> 06:12.160
She was lying on the floor.

06:12.160 --> 06:14.090
- Her condition?

06:14.090 --> 06:16.060
- She'd been shot once
in the chest at close range,

06:16.060 --> 06:18.070
as was indicated
by the powder residue

06:18.070 --> 06:19.140
around the entry wound.

06:19.140 --> 06:20.230
- Was she alive,
at that time?

06:20.230 --> 06:22.200
- The paramedics
were unable to revive her

06:22.200 --> 06:25.130
and she was pronounced dead
at the scene.

06:25.130 --> 06:28.090
- Detective, were you able
to recover a weapon?

06:28.090 --> 06:30.070
- Yes, from the floor
of the same room,

06:30.070 --> 06:32.050
several feet away
from Mrs. Armbrust.

06:32.050 --> 06:34.160
I've recovered
the .38 Special revolver,

06:34.160 --> 06:36.210
registered to the defendant.

06:36.210 --> 06:39.110
Gun residue test revealed
that he had fired the weapon.

06:39.110 --> 06:41.140
- And in the course
of your investigation,

06:41.140 --> 06:44.000
did you determine if anyone
had witnessed the shooting?

06:44.000 --> 06:47.150
- Yes, the victim's son,
Gary Armbrust,

06:47.150 --> 06:50.210
had been present and gave
a full account of events.

06:50.210 --> 06:52.100
- What did you do,
at that time?

06:52.100 --> 06:54.200
- I placed the defendant
under arrest for murder.

06:54.200 --> 06:56.080
His shirt
was splattered with blood

06:56.080 --> 06:57.210
and that was sent
to the crime lab

06:57.210 --> 07:00.090
for testing and analysis,
along with the gun.

07:00.090 --> 07:02.100
- So, you spoke to
and had an opportunity

07:02.100 --> 07:04.140
to observe Gary Armbrust
at the scene?

07:04.140 --> 07:06.140
- Yes.
- And according to your report,

07:06.140 --> 07:09.100
you observed his eyes to be
bloodshot and his speech

07:09.100 --> 07:11.020
to be slightly slurred.

07:11.020 --> 07:13.080
- He'd just witnessed
his mother's murder.

07:13.080 --> 07:15.220
He had been crying
and was extremely upset.

07:15.220 --> 07:17.160
- These symptoms
are also consistent with someone

07:17.160 --> 07:20.220
under the influence
of drugs, correct?

07:20.220 --> 07:23.040
- Sometimes, yes,
but he didn't appear to me

07:23.040 --> 07:25.190
to be under the influence
of anything other than grief.

07:25.190 --> 07:27.180
- He was never drug tested?
- No.

07:27.180 --> 07:29.180
- And Gary Armbrust's account
of these events

07:29.180 --> 07:33.120
played an instrumental role
in your decision

07:33.120 --> 07:35.170
to arrest his father
for murder?

07:35.170 --> 07:37.150
- Yes.

07:39.010 --> 07:43.020
<i>♪</i> ♪

07:43.020 --> 07:46.000
[clanging]

07:54.110 --> 07:55.200
BOBBY:
Here it is.

07:55.200 --> 07:58.050
There's a VCR up here too.

07:58.050 --> 08:01.100
Must be on
some kind of timer.

08:01.100 --> 08:04.200
We should just leave it
as is and show the police.

08:04.200 --> 08:07.150
We'll check out the rest
of the apartment.

08:07.150 --> 08:09.010
In the meantime,

08:09.010 --> 08:11.090
is there another place
that you can stay?

08:13.090 --> 08:15.150
Lucy?
- What?

08:15.150 --> 08:18.020
- Is there someone else
that you can stay?

08:18.020 --> 08:19.170
- Yeah, with my dad.

08:19.170 --> 08:22.030
- And you have no idea
who could be doing this?

08:22.030 --> 08:25.220
- [sighs] No.
- [sighs] Okay, look,

08:25.220 --> 08:27.140
I know you don't want
anybody else to find out

08:27.140 --> 08:29.170
but I'd like to bring in
Eugene and Lindsay.

08:29.170 --> 08:31.020
- No.
- Lucy.

08:31.020 --> 08:32.159
- I don't want
them all to know, Bobby.

08:32.159 --> 08:34.169
- It'll stay within the firm.

08:34.169 --> 08:36.070
Lindsay's pretty up
to speed on computers

08:36.070 --> 08:39.100
and I'll need Eugene
to knock on some doors.

08:39.100 --> 08:41.080
Let us help you.

08:46.100 --> 08:49.220
- Charlotte was
my closest friend.

08:49.220 --> 08:52.010
I knew he was gonna do something
like this.

08:52.010 --> 08:53.160
- Why do you say that,
Mrs. Roenisch?

08:53.160 --> 08:55.190
- Their marriage
was falling apart.

08:55.190 --> 08:57.220
She was planning
to leave Gordon

08:57.220 --> 08:59.180
and his ego
couldn't take it

08:59.180 --> 09:01.130
- Objection.
- Sustained.

09:01.130 --> 09:04.130
- Did you ever
hear the defendant threaten her?

09:04.130 --> 09:06.090
- Yes.

09:06.090 --> 09:09.030
About a week before her death

09:09.030 --> 09:11.130
I stopped by their house
to pick Charlotte up

09:11.130 --> 09:13.020
for a yoga class.

09:13.020 --> 09:16.000
She hated that class
because she didn't think

09:16.000 --> 09:18.010
it was really exercise.

09:18.010 --> 09:20.050
- I know this is difficult,
Mrs. Roenisch,

09:20.050 --> 09:22.030
but we need to know
about the threat.

09:22.030 --> 09:24.220
- I'm sorry.

09:24.220 --> 09:27.020
Yes, well,
when I got there,

09:27.020 --> 09:29.020
no one answered the door.

09:29.020 --> 09:31.010
So I opened it a little...

09:31.010 --> 09:33.010
to call for Charlotte
because I knew

09:33.010 --> 09:34.140
she was expecting me.

09:34.140 --> 09:36.040
- What did you see
at that time?

09:36.040 --> 09:39.040
- Gordon was holding
Charlotte's arm.

09:39.040 --> 09:41.040
She was trying to pull away

09:41.040 --> 09:43.170
and he said
that if she left him

09:43.170 --> 09:48.100
she wouldn't even
live long enough to regret it.

09:48.100 --> 09:51.080
[murmuring]

09:52.210 --> 09:54.230
- More accurately,
Gordon said

09:54.230 --> 09:56.150
that he didn't
want her to leave him

09:56.150 --> 09:58.230
and their son,
whom he believed

09:58.230 --> 10:01.070
had a drug problem
and needed both parents.

10:01.070 --> 10:03.150
- Well, yes, that's true
but it was still a threat.

10:03.150 --> 10:05.140
- And you were so concerned
the threat you overheard

10:05.140 --> 10:07.090
might be real that you
immediately contacted

10:07.090 --> 10:10.230
the police?
- No.

10:10.230 --> 10:13.090
That was my mistake.

10:13.090 --> 10:15.180
[murmuring]

10:15.180 --> 10:18.170
- Ms. Gamble.
- Hi, Gary, how you doing?

10:18.170 --> 10:20.140
- Uh, I guess I'm okay.

10:20.140 --> 10:22.070
I need to talk
to you about my testimony.

10:22.070 --> 10:23.230
- Well, you want to come back
to my office

10:23.230 --> 10:25.070
and we can run
through the questions again?

10:25.070 --> 10:26.160
- No, no, that's all right.

10:26.160 --> 10:28.200
It's just that--

10:28.200 --> 10:30.230
- What is it?

10:30.230 --> 10:34.130
- Look, I don't really
know how to say this

10:34.130 --> 10:37.090
but part of what I told you
isn't true.

10:37.090 --> 10:39.190
- Which part?

10:39.190 --> 10:43.120
- The part about my father
murdering my mother.

10:43.120 --> 10:45.080
I lied.

10:45.080 --> 10:49.070
<i>♪</i> ♪

10:54.210 --> 10:56.110
- It was an accident.

10:56.110 --> 10:58.200
- Then why did you tell
the police it was murder?

10:58.200 --> 11:01.100
- I don't know.
I was angry.

11:01.100 --> 11:03.080
- You need to do
better than that.

11:03.080 --> 11:05.110
- My father
and I were in this fight.

11:05.110 --> 11:08.090
He was so paranoid,
thinking I was using drugs.

11:08.090 --> 11:10.060
I finally got fed up.

11:10.060 --> 11:12.160
- Your father's fingerprints
are all night gun, not yours.

11:12.160 --> 11:14.070
- I had flipped out.

11:14.070 --> 11:15.230
I guess he thought I was
gonna attack him or something,

11:15.230 --> 11:17.200
because he went
and grabbed the gun

11:17.200 --> 11:19.060
he kept in the end table.

11:19.060 --> 11:21.020
- Your own father
pulled a gun on you?

11:21.020 --> 11:22.070
- Yeah.

11:22.070 --> 11:23.230
And then, I charged him

11:23.230 --> 11:26.010
and that's
when the gun went off.

11:26.010 --> 11:28.020
- If that's the truth,
why would you have even

11:28.020 --> 11:30.030
accused him
in the first place?

11:30.030 --> 11:32.200
- I-I guess I
was kind of in shock.

11:32.200 --> 11:35.160
And I thought
that if he went away for this

11:35.160 --> 11:39.140
then maybe he'd finally
be out of my life.

11:39.140 --> 11:41.000
- You really expect me
to believe this?

11:41.000 --> 11:42.150
- I know it sounds crazy

11:42.150 --> 11:44.110
but that was what was
going through my head.

11:44.110 --> 11:47.020
- Yes, and why would you wait
till now to change your story?

11:47.020 --> 11:49.190
- I just couldn't
go through with it.

11:49.190 --> 11:53.020
And this is not a story,
this is the truth.

11:53.020 --> 11:54.210
I was there, you weren't.

11:54.210 --> 11:56.120
- But I was
at the preliminary hearing

11:56.120 --> 11:58.210
where you testified that
your father shot your mother.

11:58.210 --> 12:01.040
- And that wasn't the truth.

12:01.040 --> 12:04.220
- [sighs]

12:04.220 --> 12:06.140
Have you talked
to your dad recently?

12:06.140 --> 12:09.020
- No.
- Look, I understand

12:09.020 --> 12:11.030
you might not want
to send your dad to prison--

12:11.030 --> 12:14.210
- But he didn't do it,
I did.

12:22.170 --> 12:24.110
- You don't have
to watch it, Lindsay.

12:24.110 --> 12:25.220
- No, I'm just trying
to find out how many websites

12:25.220 --> 12:27.150
it's been uploaded on to.

12:27.150 --> 12:29.060
- Wait, you mean that
there's more--

12:29.060 --> 12:31.100
- I'm afraid
that you're pretty popular.

12:34.090 --> 12:37.120
- How many times
did you watch it, Jimmy?

12:37.120 --> 12:39.060
- Not too many.

12:42.080 --> 12:45.030
[door opens]

12:45.030 --> 12:49.060
- Helen,
are we on for lunch?

12:49.060 --> 12:51.180
- No, I actually came

12:51.180 --> 12:54.010
to sort of hire a lawyer.

12:57.150 --> 13:00.120
Ellenor.

13:00.120 --> 13:03.050
Basically, he's recanting now
to save his dad.

13:03.050 --> 13:04.140
Which, since
he could now face perjury,

13:04.140 --> 13:06.190
makes me think
he needs his own lawyer.

13:06.190 --> 13:08.230
- And the reason
you want it to be me?

13:08.230 --> 13:10.090
- I want you to scare him.

13:10.090 --> 13:13.200
Make him realize
how serious perjury is.

13:13.200 --> 13:16.070
- Well, Helen,
if I represent this kid

13:16.070 --> 13:17.180
I'd be working for him,
not you.

13:17.180 --> 13:19.050
- I realize that.

13:19.050 --> 13:21.100
I just want him to hear
the legal consequences

13:21.100 --> 13:24.030
of recanting
from a defense attorney.

13:24.030 --> 13:26.200
His best interests
are also mine.

13:26.200 --> 13:28.230
- And you don't think
he's telling the truth now?

13:28.230 --> 13:31.000
- No way.
His story has been

13:31.000 --> 13:33.000
completely consistent
up until now.

13:33.000 --> 13:36.000
His statement the police
and the preliminary testimony

13:36.000 --> 13:37.150
corroborate
the physical evidence.

13:37.150 --> 13:40.000
This case is tight.

13:40.000 --> 13:41.220
Will you, at least,
talk to him?

13:47.010 --> 13:48.100
- Locks have not
been tampered with,

13:48.100 --> 13:50.030
no sign of break-ins
with the windows.

13:50.030 --> 13:52.010
- What about from above
the shower where the VCR was?

13:52.010 --> 13:53.100
- A secured crawl space.

13:53.100 --> 13:55.040
This was done
by somebody with access.

13:55.040 --> 13:58.070
You had any parties, Lucy?
Friends over?

13:58.070 --> 14:00.030
- I have friends
over sometimes but I--

14:00.030 --> 14:03.000
- What about that Boston
Celtic guy, basketball players,

14:03.000 --> 14:05.140
what's his name, Hot Rod?
- Rodman?

14:05.140 --> 14:07.050
- What about Frank?

14:07.050 --> 14:09.110
- None of my friends
would've planted a camera.

14:09.110 --> 14:11.000
[door opens]

14:11.000 --> 14:12.200
- New case.
No money.

14:12.200 --> 14:16.140
- It's a favor.
Commonwealth thanks you.

14:16.140 --> 14:19.010
- Oh, my God!
- Now what?

14:19.010 --> 14:20.050
- It isn't you.

14:20.050 --> 14:21.160
It's Jimmy.
- What?

14:21.160 --> 14:23.080
- I just tapped
into the Boston Buff website

14:23.080 --> 14:26.070
to see if you were listed
but, damn, I lost it.

14:26.070 --> 14:27.210
- Uh, what's Boston Buff?

14:27.210 --> 14:29.140
- The Boston Buff society,
court buffs.

14:29.140 --> 14:31.210
They're basically retired people
who follow trials

14:31.210 --> 14:35.050
and they rank lawyers.
Here it is.

14:35.050 --> 14:37.110
Seems like
they went to gossip now.

14:37.110 --> 14:38.180
"Attorney James Berluti

14:38.180 --> 14:40.080
has been making
a little chamber music

14:40.080 --> 14:42.070
with Judge Roberta Kittleson."

14:42.070 --> 14:44.130
- What?
That's ridiculous.

14:48.220 --> 14:51.160
[stammers]
That's trick photography!

14:55.220 --> 14:57.130
- Jimmy, in my office.

15:03.060 --> 15:05.170
- Her own witness
is now backing my client's story

15:05.170 --> 15:07.150
and Ms. Gamble's the only one
