30:27.100 --> 30:29.000
- Witness for the prosecution?

30:29.000 --> 30:30.070
- We relied on the son, Mark,

30:30.070 --> 30:32.110
he changes his testimony
at trial,

30:32.110 --> 30:34.200
instant reasonable doubt.
- With the threat of perjury?

30:34.200 --> 30:36.130
- Oh,
he won't do much for that.

30:36.130 --> 30:38.070
We both know that so does he.

30:38.070 --> 30:41.190
If the recanting is ruled timely
he could get off altogether,

30:41.190 --> 30:44.020
which his lawyer told him.

30:44.020 --> 30:45.160
[sighs]

30:45.160 --> 30:49.050
I've lost another murderer.

30:49.050 --> 30:51.050
I can't believe this.

30:51.050 --> 30:53.100
First, I lose a guy
who dices up a nun.

30:53.100 --> 30:55.040
Now--
- Can you recall forensics,

30:55.040 --> 30:57.010
prove it couldn't have happened
the way they're saying?

30:57.010 --> 30:59.170
- I can't prove it,
not beyond a reasonable doubt.

31:01.050 --> 31:03.030
I can't believe this.
- Yeah, well,

31:03.030 --> 31:04.230
I wouldn't go
witness for the prosecution,

31:04.230 --> 31:08.120
it's too desperate
and I think it's too late.

31:08.120 --> 31:10.190
Just give it your best shot.

31:10.190 --> 31:12.110
- Hm.

31:12.110 --> 31:15.220
There's got to be a way.

31:15.220 --> 31:17.220
I'm gonna find a way.

31:25.060 --> 31:27.020
- A hundred tapes?

31:27.020 --> 31:30.140
- He had other cameras
planted in other places.

31:30.140 --> 31:34.210
- So, he has videos of me...
doing everything?

31:34.210 --> 31:39.050
- I've arranged
to have them destroyed.

31:39.050 --> 31:43.100
- But they could've already
been uploaded on websites?

31:43.100 --> 31:47.080
- Yes.

31:47.080 --> 31:49.230
- Will he go to jail?
- He's being arraigned today.

31:49.230 --> 31:53.090
I told Jimmy to cover it,
but, Lucy,

31:53.090 --> 31:55.160
the law--
stealing electricity,

31:55.160 --> 31:59.060
maybe trespass, he--
he won't do any time.

32:01.050 --> 32:02.030
<i>[somber music]</i>

32:02.030 --> 32:04.030
- Hey.

32:06.000 --> 32:07.120
- What if my father--

32:07.120 --> 32:08.210
- You said
he doesn't own a computer.

32:08.210 --> 32:10.030
- Yeah, but what
if somebody makes a tape

32:10.030 --> 32:11.040
off of the computer and--

32:11.040 --> 32:14.190
- Look, you did nothing wrong.

32:14.190 --> 32:16.200
<i>♪</i> ♪

32:16.200 --> 32:18.030
- Well, can I sue him?

32:18.030 --> 32:21.030
- Well, we could

32:21.030 --> 32:24.210
but he's--he's--he's pretty
judgment proof.

32:24.210 --> 32:26.060
He did lose his job.

32:26.060 --> 32:28.160
I mean,
that's--that's something.

32:28.160 --> 32:31.090
<i>♪</i> ♪

32:31.090 --> 32:33.140
- Okay.
[sniffles]

32:33.140 --> 32:37.020
Um,
I should get back to work.

32:37.020 --> 32:40.220
- Uh, you want to take
the day off?

32:40.220 --> 32:44.050
- And do what, go home?

32:44.050 --> 32:45.150
Nah, I'm fine.

32:45.150 --> 32:48.030
Yeah, I've got a lot
of work to do.

32:48.030 --> 32:50.030
I'm totally fine.

32:50.030 --> 32:53.040
- Lucy, the reason
you feel so violated

32:53.040 --> 32:56.060
is because you have been.

32:56.060 --> 33:00.060
And this is no time
to play tough.

33:00.060 --> 33:02.100
Look at me.

33:02.100 --> 33:05.050
Maybe this isn't the equivalent
to rape,

33:05.050 --> 33:09.190
but that man
took your privacy from you

33:09.190 --> 33:14.050
and it's not nothing.

33:14.050 --> 33:17.130
It wouldn't be a bad idea
to get some counseling.

33:19.130 --> 33:21.110
- Okay.

33:23.040 --> 33:25.040
- And it wouldn't be
a bad idea

33:25.040 --> 33:27.010
to lean on people here
a little.

33:31.040 --> 33:35.010
- It's just that I feel like--
[crying]

33:35.010 --> 33:36.230
- I know.

33:40.180 --> 33:42.160
I know.

33:44.060 --> 33:48.080
- Two different versions
from the same witness.

33:48.080 --> 33:51.000
How can you know
which one is true?

33:51.000 --> 33:53.060
The state will probably stand up
here, in a few minutes,

33:53.060 --> 33:55.110
and try to convince you
that Gary Armbrust

33:55.110 --> 33:58.130
suddenly felt bad.

33:58.130 --> 34:00.190
Didn't want to see
his father convicted.

34:00.190 --> 34:03.100
Decided to change his story.

34:03.100 --> 34:04.160
Now,
you've heard Ms. Gamble

34:04.160 --> 34:07.030
toss out witness
for the prosecution,

34:07.030 --> 34:12.050
they did it together
for the insurance.

34:12.050 --> 34:16.190
Now, that theory came
at the 11th hour, didn't it?

34:16.190 --> 34:20.050
Why?

34:20.050 --> 34:22.060
Desperation.

34:22.060 --> 34:25.190
Because the only eyewitness
told you it was an accident.

34:25.190 --> 34:28.010
Told you
he attacked the defendant,

34:28.010 --> 34:29.130
causing the gun to go off.

34:29.130 --> 34:31.060
Do I really need to be
standing up here

34:31.060 --> 34:34.130
arguing reasonable doubt?

34:34.130 --> 34:38.000
The state wants you to believe
Gary Armbrust is truthful

34:38.000 --> 34:41.150
when he says one thing,
but he has no credibility

34:41.150 --> 34:45.080
when he's saying another.

34:45.080 --> 34:47.230
But you can't
have it both ways.

34:51.010 --> 34:53.230
[murmuring]

34:57.040 --> 34:59.040
- Yes,
we have two versions now,

34:59.040 --> 35:00.200
from one witness.

35:00.200 --> 35:02.140
It's up to you to weigh
the credibility

35:02.140 --> 35:04.200
and circumstances of each.

35:04.200 --> 35:08.080
You're free to discredit
recantation and find

35:08.080 --> 35:11.050
that the truth
lies in his original accusation

35:11.050 --> 35:13.110
and I'll tell you
why you should.

35:13.110 --> 35:15.060
Gary told the officers
at the scene

35:15.060 --> 35:17.100
that his father
murdered his mother.

35:17.100 --> 35:19.050
He said
that they had a bitter argument.

35:19.050 --> 35:20.170
She threatened to leave him

35:20.170 --> 35:23.050
and they shot her
point blank in the chest.

35:23.050 --> 35:26.220
Now, Gary testified
to the same facts,

35:26.220 --> 35:30.060
under oath,
at the preliminary hearing,

35:30.060 --> 35:34.010
not one inconsistency
in any of the details.

35:34.010 --> 35:36.210
Every last bit of his account

35:36.210 --> 35:41.000
was consistent with every piece
of physical evidence.

35:41.000 --> 35:44.110
Then suddenly,
just as the trial begins,

35:44.110 --> 35:46.210
he has a change of heart

35:46.210 --> 35:49.200
and I guess
we can understand.

35:49.200 --> 35:52.040
He's already lost his mother,

35:52.040 --> 35:55.060
he doesn't want
to lose his father, does he?

35:55.060 --> 35:58.210
And, well...

35:58.210 --> 36:02.100
maybe he's found a way
to even forgive his dad.

36:04.020 --> 36:06.020
But we can't.

36:06.020 --> 36:08.140
A woman is dead.

36:08.140 --> 36:11.040
Charlotte Armbrust
deserves to have us

36:11.040 --> 36:12.120
stand up for the truth,

36:12.120 --> 36:15.130
even if her son no longer can.

36:15.130 --> 36:19.010
Charlotte doesn't have
a voice anymore.

36:19.010 --> 36:22.010
You do.

36:22.010 --> 36:23.140
We all know what happened.

36:27.150 --> 36:30.040
Prints only belonging
to the defendant,

36:30.040 --> 36:33.050
blood spattered only
on the defendant,

36:33.050 --> 36:34.170
we have the threats.

36:34.170 --> 36:38.070
That man committed murder.

36:38.070 --> 36:40.150
And his son,

36:40.150 --> 36:42.160
well, he suddenly decided
he wants him

36:42.160 --> 36:46.100
to get away with it.

36:46.100 --> 36:48.040
Do you?

36:53.060 --> 36:56.030
- 32623,
Commonwealth versus Conley.

36:56.030 --> 36:59.020
Trespass,
theft of electricity.

36:59.020 --> 37:00.130
- Robert Olson
for the defendant.

37:00.130 --> 37:02.040
- Theft of electricity,

37:02.040 --> 37:03.200
are they prosecuting
that these days?

37:03.200 --> 37:06.020
- Your Honor, the defendant
is a superintendent

37:06.020 --> 37:07.160
at an apartment complex.

37:07.160 --> 37:09.220
He installed cameras
to tape one of the dwellers.

37:09.220 --> 37:13.000
Then, he uploaded her naked
images on the Internet.

37:13.000 --> 37:16.120
Theft of electricity--
- Hold on a second.

37:19.060 --> 37:22.220
Well, well, well,
Mr. Conley,

37:22.220 --> 37:24.220
did you get the wrong judge.

37:24.220 --> 37:26.170
OLESON: We'll waive reading,
Your Honor.

37:26.170 --> 37:29.040
- Why don't you wave good-bye,
while you're at it?

37:29.040 --> 37:33.060
Did you have fun invading
a young woman's privacy?

37:33.060 --> 37:34.200
- Excuse me, Your Honor?

37:34.200 --> 37:37.020
- Council,
you speak when I ask you to.

37:38.210 --> 37:42.060
Uploading her naked images
on the Internet.

37:42.060 --> 37:46.020
Funny, I just discovered things
about me on the Internet.

37:46.020 --> 37:50.120
Maybe there's stuff
about all of us, who knows?

37:54.070 --> 37:56.200
Take off your pants.
OLSEN: Your Honor!

37:56.200 --> 37:59.220
- Bailiff, would you please take
Mr. Olsen into custody.

37:59.220 --> 38:02.030
He is in contempt.
- What?

38:02.030 --> 38:06.210
- You want another chance?
Then shut your mouth!

38:06.210 --> 38:10.010
Mr. Conley,
drop your pants, right now

38:10.010 --> 38:12.110
or I will add contempt
to your charges

38:12.110 --> 38:15.140
and you will go straight
to a jail cell!

38:17.140 --> 38:20.060
I am going to count to three!

38:20.060 --> 38:23.160
One, two--

38:23.160 --> 38:26.160
[murmuring]

38:26.160 --> 38:29.160
[gallery gasps]

38:29.160 --> 38:31.180
[murmuring]

38:31.180 --> 38:35.020
No underwear.
Figures.

38:35.020 --> 38:36.210
And nothing much
else, I might add.

38:36.210 --> 38:39.190
[laughter]

38:41.060 --> 38:44.110
- Do you feel violated,
Mr. Conley?

38:44.110 --> 38:46.050
Exposed?

38:46.050 --> 38:48.190
How does it feel?

38:48.190 --> 38:50.100
Would you turn around
and face the gallery?

38:50.100 --> 38:52.050
Show them
what you haven't got.

38:52.050 --> 38:53.170
- Your Honor,
even I have to say,

38:53.170 --> 38:55.020
this is a little bit
irregular.

38:55.020 --> 38:58.150
- Tough!

38:58.150 --> 39:01.200
Turn around, Mr. Conley.

39:04.020 --> 39:07.000
[murmuring]

39:09.100 --> 39:12.080
[women exclaiming]

39:18.000 --> 39:20.090
Take Mr. Conley.
Put him in jail.

39:20.090 --> 39:21.160
We had can arraign him
again tomorrow.

39:21.160 --> 39:23.030
Would you call the next
case, please?

39:23.030 --> 39:25.170
Leave your pants,
right there...

39:25.170 --> 39:28.010
at your ankles!

39:29.060 --> 39:32.050
[murmuring]

39:32.050 --> 39:36.040
- Case number 32624,
Commonwealth versus Waterman,

39:36.040 --> 39:40.020
criminal violation,
illegal disposal of toxic waste.

39:50.130 --> 39:52.090
- That was different.

39:52.090 --> 39:53.220
- Imagine his luck,

39:53.220 --> 39:56.030
getting me for a judge,
of all days.

39:56.030 --> 39:57.110
- Are you okay?

39:57.110 --> 40:00.130
- I am so--

40:00.130 --> 40:02.200
you know, I am no prude.

40:02.200 --> 40:06.110
I would have no problems
taking the bench naked,

40:06.110 --> 40:08.190
so long as it were my choice,
but to be--

40:08.190 --> 40:11.040
- Well, hopefully the laws
on Internet stuff

40:11.040 --> 40:12.140
will start to change.

40:12.140 --> 40:15.000
Maybe the test
case will come before you.

40:15.000 --> 40:17.200
- [sighs]

40:17.200 --> 40:19.160
It did bother you,
reading all of that stuff

40:19.160 --> 40:21.110
didn't it, Jimmy?

40:21.110 --> 40:25.000
- Yeah, but, you know,
it's my mother's influence.

40:25.000 --> 40:26.190
In the back of my mind,
I guess I was still

40:26.190 --> 40:30.150
hoping you were virgin.

40:30.150 --> 40:33.150
- Yes.
